Then, I felt the fill was difficult to nail down given all the gaps the very pervasive theme left, and I thought many of the clues were a little questionable (e.g. never seen "AM/PM" as a toggle on a traditional digital clock, "asps" is too specific an answer for the Indiana Jones clue, I've exceedingly rarely had to prepay for my reservations at hotels and restaurants).

All in all, this Thursday took me as much time as some of my longer Saturday puzzles, but I usually enjoy Saturday puzzles a lot more. That's okay--I've noticed sometimes I just really "vibe" with the architect, and sometimes I just really don't.

